<title>UK: C&amp;W hires Lerwill as fd, promotes Olsen.</title>
<headline>C&amp;W hires Lerwill as fd, promotes Olsen.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Britain's Cable and Wireless Plc said on Thursday it would hire Robert Lerwill to become its finance director, replacing Rod Olsen who has already been promoted to deputy chief executive.</p>
<p>In a statement the company said that 44-year-old Lerwill, who is moving from WPP Group Plc after 10 years in the top finance job there, would report direct to chief executive Dick Brown.</p>
<p>Brown said C&amp;W believed Lerwill would &quot;help deliver real benefits to our shareholders&quot;.</p>
